.TH GEN-HEADER "1" "December 2025" "gen-header 202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gen-header \- Bash script header generator with metadata and boilerplate code
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gen-header
[\\fI\\,COMMAND\\fR] [\\fI\\,OPTIONS\\fR] [\\fI\\,SCRIPT_NAME\\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gen-header
is a comprehensive bash script header and boilerplate code generator that automates the creation of standardized script headers with metadata, copyright information, directory structure variables, function templates, and environment variable definitions. It supports multiple script types (system, user, profile), generates version timestamps, and provides commands for updating existing scripts with new header information.
.PP
The script simplifies bash script development by providing automatic header generation with metadata fields (version, author, copyright, license), environment variable generation for directory structures, function template generation with standard patterns, header replacement in existing scripts without manual editing, support for various license types (WTFPL, GPL, MIT, etc.), script type templates (system scripts, user scripts, profile scripts), and automatic version timestamp generation (YYYYMMDDHHMM-git format).
.PP
gen-header is particularly useful for developers maintaining consistent script formats, system administrators creating standardized automation scripts, projects requiring uniform script documentation, teams needing consistent header metadata across scripts, and maintaining version control information in script headers.
.SH USAGE
.B gen-header head myscript
.PP
Generate header for myscript with default metadata.
.PP
.B gen-header folders MYAPP
.PP
Generate directory structure environment variables for MYAPP.
.PP
.B gen-header functions myscript
.PP
Generate function templates for myscript.
.PP
.B gen-header replace myscript.sh "old" "new"
.PP
Replace text in myscript.sh header.
